column1: Fix A2 converted 360 export to support master only
column28:
*Desc:*

Legacy export for 360 was designed only around productized exports (exports linked from a product via a product details) and not around master exports. However we no longer support A2 links to export page from product details so need to make sure master exports work as expected. We should fix all these issues for 360 so that converted export work.

 

*Dev Notes:*
 * One noted issue was a nullPointer exception if product is null in one of the 360 calls

column1: Legacy Wav 16 Downconvert Exception
column28:
*Desc:*

There is a periodic issue that pops up for wav 16 downconverts where the conversion fails due to a sox issue. On the conversion is suggesting that the file has issues when this pops up but we have been unable to simulate this re-using the file. The working theory is that the there is an issue with the temp file on the AOMA side which is causing the issue. This ticket is to investigate the issue further (first step adding logs so we have a little more information)

 

*Notes:*

Seems to trigger more often when doing downconvert wav 24 from direct upload.

Confirmed this is an issue with directUpload workflows, the files are not in the temp location (direct migration) at the time of the conversion call. Simple upload seems to be working fine.

column1: Batch Offering Mismatch of ConversionTypeIds
column28:
*Desc:*

If a user does not have all the permissions tied to conversiontype list we will hide some of the conversions and store an array value on the UI selector (1,2,3 ETC. instead of CT #). On the backend though we do use the full list of CT's which can cause can cause the wrong CT to be used. We should either have CT values be passed to the backend or make sure both lists are always in sync.

 

*Notes:*
 * For example if user is missing CONVERT_AUDIO_TIER_2 permission, if they sent a WAV conversion it will use CT 12188 instead because of this mismatch

column1: Product Status UI: Update how we populate assiocated Master Status for Video Bundles
column28:
We need to update how Video Bundles populate the product status page as there currently is an issue where vsc's are not being correctly displayed from the linked products causing grps publishing to be halted. A second flow needs to be added that handles video bundle products by gathering the linked products of that bundle and checking each one for a vsc that should be populating the master status table instead of the vic.



AC:
 VSC's should be shown in the associated master status section instead of vics when the vscs are present in the linked products of the bundle.

column1: Batch Offering (Old Interface) - Searching only ISRC 's not returning the entire results - Analysis of the issue
column28:
*+Current Behavior:+* 
When a user searches with only ISRC's the results are not displayed completely , But when the user searches for ProductNo + IRSC (using the same ISRC) it returns the results for those ISRC's. which were not displayed when only isrc was searched.

Eg.
When 10 ISRC searched only 6 displayed and 4 not displayed, When that 4 are searched with ProductNo + IRSC it gets displayed.

*+Expected Behavior:+*
If a user searches only for ISRC's it should search & return results for those ISRC's.

column1: Bulk VSC Register Script : Enahcement to support ImagePath for VSC
column28:
As of now - *Bulk VSC Extract&Register script* supports VSC registration in bulk via CatalogKy, VideoMasterId, TimeCode.
 Add another script *bulkVSCRegisterWithImagePath*

+*Usage:*+
 2 input parameters : 
                     _1st Param_: Path to the input CSV file
                     _2nd Param_: AOMA User ID
 ~/*bulkVSCRegisterWithImagePath* <_*PATH_TO_bulkVSCResgisterInputFile.csv*_> <_*userId*_>

*CSV file data format:* CatalogKy,VideoMasterId,ImagePath

*AC:*
 When script is executed with valid input CSV file, for the supplied Product :
 A. VSC Master is created
 B. VSC is registered with the same image provided via the CSV file
 C. The VSC master is linked with Product
 D. EOM message sent for the registered VSC master creation or linking with PROD with *assetSuppressFlag=Y*.

*In case*, the PRODUCT has already linked VSC - the existing VSC will be HotSwapped and VSC Status will be maintained.

column1: New XSD Setup : MediaInfoDescripto.xsd
column28:
Execute following set of activities:
 *1. Add XSD to Nexus:*
 Updload *MediaInfoDescriptor.xsd* to Nexus : schema/conversion/1.0

*2.  Add new binding file*(at */setup/jaxb*) - To resolve the name collision :  MediaInfoDescriptor.jxb

*3. aoma.svc > build.xml changes:*
 +A. Add new directory location to import the new XSD:+
      <target name="init">
              - - -
              <target name="init">
              - - -
       </target>

+B. Get new XSD to above created location:+
      <target name="resolve" depends="init-ivy, resolve-build" description="Resolve dependencies">
              - - -
              <get src="${library}/schema/conversion/1.0/MediaInfoDescriptor.xsd" dest="${src.schema.dir}/aoma/mediainfo/MediaInfoDescriptor.xsd" usetimestamp="true" />
              <copy tofile="${src.schema.dir}/aoma/mediainfo/xjc-mediainfo-binding.xjb" file="setup/jaxb/xjc-mediainfo-binding.xjb" />
              - - -
       </target>

+C. Generate Java Source file from XSD:+

      <target name="generate" depends="resolve" description="Generate code">
              - - -
              <xjc destdir="${generated.src.dir}" package="com.sonybmg.aoma.schema.mediainfo"> 
                           <arg value="-npa"/> 
                           <arg value="-extension"/> 
                           -<binding file="setup/jaxb/xjc-mediainfo-binding.jxb" />- 
                           <binding file="${src.schema.dir}/aoma/mediainfo/xjc-mediainfo-binding.xjb" />                           
                           <schema dir="${src.schema.dir}/aoma/mediainfo" includes="*.xsd" /> 
                           <depends dir="${src.schema.dir}/aoma/mediainfo" includes="*.xsd" /> 
                           <produces dir="${generated.src.dir}/com/sonybmg/aoma/schema/mediainfo" includes="*.java" /> 
              </xjc>
              - - -
       </target>

column1: Vantage Auto-Correction in AOMA2 Registration (Flag On Testing)
column28:
As a QC Reg User, when I am on AOMA and submit a video for registration, then:

1) the video should be converted and converted video should be registered with the corresponding descriptor file

2) the source video should be copied to the GMP shared folder with the corresponding -descriptor file-  MD5 Hash File

 

*CT ID* 12194

+*User Story Details:*+
 * Descriptor Files will be a parsed version of -Vidchecker and- Vantage files

 

*Acceptance Criteria:*

1)

Given as a QC Reg User,

when I am on AOMA, submitting a video for registration,

then AOMA should register the converted video 

 

2)

Given as a QC Reg User,

when I am on AOMA, submitting a video for registration,

then AOMA should register the converted video descriptor file 

 

3)

Given as a QC Reg User,

when I am on AOMA, submitting a video for registration,

then AOMA should copy the source video -AND descriptor file- into the GMP Shared folder 

4)

Given as a QC Reg User,

when I am on AOMA, after registering a video,

then AOMA should email the descriptor 

5)

Given as a Non-QC Reg User,

when I am on AOMA, submitting a video for registration,

then AOMA should register the source video following the current process

 
----
+*Dev Process:*+

CT A: Descriptor (exists)

CT B: Video Conversion (Until we get the CT from GMP/MC - dummy CT/copy conversion/ CT 12192)

 
 * Source Video -> CT A -> *Source Video Descriptor* 
 * Source Video ->  CT B - > *Converted Video* 
 * *Converted Video* -> CT A -> *Converted Video Descriptor*

+*Reg Process: (Product Reg)*+ 
 * QC User Submits Source Video -> *Converted Video & Converted Video Descriptor*

+*GMP Shared Folder/QC Files: (Master Only Reg)*+
 * -Source Descriptor- 
 * Source Video
 * MD5 Hash File

+*Email:*+
 * *Converted Descriptor File*
 * *Source Video* *Descriptor File*
 * Source Master Number 
 * Converted Master Number

+*Flag*+:
 * com.sonymusic.aoma.registration.autoQcWorkflowEnabled

 
----
+_Pending GMP Approval/Requirement_+
 * *{color:#ff0000}Another file that shows the descriptor delta? (For GMP/Mike C){color}*
 ** *{color:#ff0000}No delta{color}*
 ** *{color:#ff0000}We need both descriptors in the email{color}* 
 ** {color:#ff0000}*Only copy source video and source descriptor to GMP*{color}
 * {color:#ff0000}*Do we need this for all QC Reg users, or is it limited to a limited number of QC Reg users based on permissions?*{color}
 ** {color:#ff0000}*All QC REG Users only*{color}**
 * SMEJ Video workflow to go through this process as well (Out of Scope)

column1: Decommission Quick Convert
Batch Export button on Mobile Audio Manager should be permission-driven
column28:
'+*Description*+

In the Mobile Audio Manager, there is a Batch Export button on the page. When a user clicks this button, it redirects them to the Batch Offering page. This button should be permission controlled.

The required permission is named *TEMP_LEGACY_BATCH_OFFERING*
• If a user has the *TEMP_LEGACY_BATCH_OFFERING* permission, they should be able to see the Batch Export button and click it to navigate to the Batch Offering page.
• If a user does not have this permission, the Batch Export button should not be visible.

+*User Story*+
*As a* user,
*I want* the Batch Export button in Mobile Audio Manager to be permission controlled by the *TEMP_LEGACY_BATCH_OFFERING* permission,
*so that* only authorized users can view and access the Batch Offering page through this button.

+*Acceptance Criteria*+

1. Visibility based on permission
*Given* a user has the *TEMP_LEGACY_BATCH_OFFERING* permission
*When* they access the Mobile Audio Manager page
*Then* the Batch Export button is visible to them.

2. Navigation when permission granted
*Given* a user has the *TEMP_LEGACY_BATCH_OFFERING* permission
*When* they click the Batch Export button
*Then* the system redirects them to the Batch Offering page.

3. No visibility without permission
*Given* a user does not have the *TEMP_LEGACY_BATCH_OFFERING* permission
*When* they access the Mobile Audio Manager page
*Then* the Batch Export button is *NOT* displayed to them.

column1: CMG Revoke On Export Needs to Filter By Side Sequence
column28:
*Desc:*

When a user has a virtually side (or track?) linked ddp and blue-ray disc and attempt to export both assets to CES:
 * We create two export jobs
 * Each export has its own ces key stored export_keys db table

The issue that was noted was that the first export was not showing up in the system. This seems to be due to the fact the export key for the first export is getting revoked due to second ones filtering out for old jobs. When we check for active keys we filter by masterId and productId and both exports share this because they are both virtually linked to the same master.
{code:java}
CMGPackager.java

select k.original_export_delivery_status_id from export_keys k where k.product_id = ? and k.master_id = ? and k.export_key_status_id = ?{code}
To fix the issue we should also filter by the side sequence to make sure extra keys are not being deleted for this case.

*Dev Notes:*
 * The class to change is CMGPackager.java in the AOMA project
 ** In the doPackaging method we cancel out the old keys on line 448.
 ** We need to update this to include sequence in the db query look up for which keys should be revokved

*AC:*

When a user has a virtually side linked ddp and dvdddp and attempt to export both assets to CES:
 * We create two export jobs
 * Each export has its own ces key stored export_keys db table
 * Both export keys should remain active 

If a user exports one of those assets again
 * Only the assets tied to that sequence should be deleted.
 * (Also try virtual masters with multiple sides - example product from the dpsa was virtually side linked 2 ddps + 1 blu-ray disc.)
